Vladimir Putin is under pressure to put 'peacekeeping' troops on the ground in Ukraine as NATO accused the Kremlin of posing 'a threat to the international order'.

Separatists supporting Moscow in eastern Ukraine called on the Russian president to put soldiers into Donetsk and Lugansk regions to maintain order. 

A call for peacekeeping forces also came from the head of the Russian parliament's defence committee Admiral Vladislav Komoyedov.

